The paper deals with the task of lipreading, which involves analyzing visual features from video frames and predicting text. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of deep learning techniques such as spatiotemporal convolutions and recurrent networks suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves training a model end-to-end, which could be relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
